" <div class=\"graphic\">",
"  <div class=\"figure\" style=\"width: 470px\">",
"   <div class=\"ttl\">",
"    Mechanism of acromioclavicular joint injury",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 438px; height: 497px; background-image: url(data:image/jpeg;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    Injury to the acromioclavicular (AC) joint usually occurs from direct trauma to the superior or lateral aspect of the shoulder with the arm adducted, such as falling onto the shoulder. Greater force increases the risk of injury.",
